---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'May 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
    title="Cookie and storage policy"
    description="Cookies, local storage, and similar technologies used on the LSCSS documentation site."
>
    <main class="page-shell">
        <section class="site-hero">
            <p class="eyebrow">Site policy</p>

            <h1>Cookie and storage policy</h1>

            <p class="intro">
                This page explains cookies and browser storage used on
                <strong>lscss.crayonsandco.de</strong>. We aim to be plain about what is
                set, why, and how long it lasts. For wider data use (including analytics),
                see the <a href="/privacy/">privacy policy</a>.
            </p>

            <p class="intro">
                <small>Last updated: {lastUpdated}.</small>
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="content-block">
            <h2>Do we use cookie banners?</h2>
            <p>
                No. This site does not set non-essential cookies for advertising or
                cross-site tracking. Analytics on the live site uses
                <a href="https://umami.is/">Umami Cloud</a> in a
                <strong>cookieless</strong> mode, so we do not ask for consent for
                marketing or analytics cookies. If that changes, we will update this page
                and the privacy policy.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="content-block">
            <h2>Cookies</h2>
            <p>
                At the time of writing, the LSCSS documentation site does
                <strong>not</strong> set first-party HTTP cookies for visitors. We do not
                use cookie-based session tracking, advertising pixels, or social embeds
                that set third-party cookies on ordinary documentation pages.
            </p>
            <p>
                Umami analytics (production only) does not rely on visitor cookies; see
                <a href="/privacy/">privacy policy</a> for what is collected.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="content-block">
            <h2>Local storage and similar APIs</h2>
            <p>
                Some features store a preference in your browser using
                <code>localStorage</code> (not a cookie, but similar in practice for
                visitors). These are functional, not used for advertising.
            </p>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong><code>lscss-theme</code></strong> — remembers light or dark
                    theme if you change it; lasts until you clear site data in the browser.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Playground editors (where present)</strong> — may save draft
                    code locally on pages that include a live playground; lasts until you
                    clear site data.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Umami (via analytics script)</strong> — may use storage only to
                    honour a disable flag if you opt out in Umami’s UI; not set by default
                    for normal visits.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="content-block">
            <h2>How to clear or block storage</h2>
            <p>
                You can clear cookies and site data in your browser settings for
                <code>lscss.crayonsandco.de</code>. Blocking all storage may reset your
                theme preference. Privacy extensions and ad blockers may block the Umami
                script or its network requests; the site still works without analytics.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="content-block">
            <h2>Related policies</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="/privacy/">Privacy policy</a></li>
                <li><a href="/accessibility/">Accessibility statement</a></li>
                <li><a href="/ai/">AI and this site</a></li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>
